<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='138914' id='t-138914'>and you told me a story.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='140652' id='t-140652'>And I said -- very last minute -- you know, 
you really should share that story.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 2:35
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='144531' id='t-144531'>SS: Oh, yeah.
PM: What was that story?</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 2:37
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='146281' id='t-146281'>SS: Well, it's an important part of the 
journey. So I had -- TEDWomen --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='149546' id='t-149546'>the original one was in D.C. -- so I live here, 
so I had gotten on a plane the day before,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='153355' id='t-153355'>and my daughter was three, she was 
clinging to my leg: &quot;Mommy, don't go.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='158404' id='t-158404'>And Pat's a friend, and so, not related 
